  indicates that small changes to water\textendash channel interactions can
  alter the free energy barrier for ion permeation. These results, illustrating
  polarization effects present in the complex electrostatic environment of the
  gA channel, have broad implications for revising proposed mechanisms of ion
  permeation and selectivity in a variety of ion channels.%
