  simultaneously, rather breaking one of these interactions and forming another
  nearby (a mechanism we term dynamic shuttling). Further simulations with
  small molecules chosen to modify these interactions yielded binding
  affinities and key structural features of binding consistent with subsequent
  NMR experiments, suggesting the potential for MD-based strategies to
  facilitate the rational design of small molecules that bind with disordered
